# arxiv-voice

Generate a deep paper overview and a narrated research brief from a PDF.

## What It Does

- extracts text from a paper PDF
- creates chunk-level analytical notes with a local LLM through Ollama
- synthesizes those notes into a comprehensive `overview.md`
- rewrites the overview into a spoken script
- optionally renders local audio with macOS `say`

The first implementation is optimized for a single-speaker research brief. Podcast-style multi-speaker output is the next extension point, but it is not wired yet.

## Requirements

- Python 3.9+
- [`uv`](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv) or `pip`
- [Ollama](https://ollama.com/) running locally with a model installed
- macOS `say` if you want local narration audio

## Quickstart

```bash
uv sync
uv run arxiv-voice run 2603.14473v1.pdf
```

Useful flags:

```bash
uv run arxiv-voice run 2603.14473v1.pdf --model llama3.2:latest --page-limit 4
uv run arxiv-voice run 2603.14473v1.pdf --no-audio
uv run arxiv-voice extract 2603.14473v1.pdf
uv run arxiv-voice overview runs/<run-id>
uv run arxiv-voice narrate runs/<run-id> --voice Samantha
```

## Output Layout

Each run is written to `runs/<timestamp>-<paper-slug>/` and includes:

- `source.pdf`
- `paper.txt`
- `metadata.json`
- `sections.json`
- `analysis/chunk-*.md`
- `overview.md`
- `spoken_overview.txt`
- `audio/chunks/*.aiff`
- `audio/research_brief.aiff`
- `manifest.json`
